{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17606104","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17606104"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:08:22+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:08:22+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15892"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15892","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15892"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.35,0.22,0.09,0.26,0.09]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8583"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72535"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8583","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8583"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15892"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58005"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"3618"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"10623"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20574"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20575"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72535","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72535"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring pregnancy, steroid hormone production requires cooperation between the placenta and foetus in a process known as the foeto-placental unit.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following enzymes is present in both placental and foetal tissues?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Aromatase","Sulfatase","16 alpha-hydroxylase","17 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase","3 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe foeto-placental unit requires cooperation between placental and fetal tissues for complete steroid hormone synthesis. \u003Cstrong\u003EAromatase\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily found in placental tissue, where it converts androgens to oestrogens. \u003Cstrong\u003ESulfatase\u003C/strong\u003E is also predominantly placental. \u003Cstrong\u003E16 alpha-hydroxylase\u003C/strong\u003E is exclusively present in the foetal liver. \u003Cstrong\u003E17 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase\u003C/strong\u003E is found in both placental and foetal tissues, where it catalyses the interconversion of androstenedione and testosterone, as well as estrone and estradiol. \u003Cstrong\u003E3 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase\u003C/strong\u003E is mainly placental.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The placenta and foetus work together in steroid hormone synthesis through shared enzymes","17 beta-hydroxysteroid dehydrogenase is present in both placental and foetal tissues for steroid metabolism","The placenta lacks certain enzymes like 16 alpha-hydroxylase, requiring fetal cooperation for complete steroid synthesis"],"references":["Napso T, Yong HEJ, Lopez-Tello J, Sferruzzi-Perri AN. The Role of Placental Hormones in Mediating Maternal Adaptations to Support Pregnancy and Lactation. Front Physiol. 2018 Aug 17;9:1091. doi: 10.3389/fphys.2018.01091. PMID: 30174608; PMCID: PMC6108594","Newbern D, Freemark M. Placental hormones and the control of maternal metabolism and fetal growth. Curr Opin Endocrinol Diabetes Obes. 2011 Dec;18(6):409-16. doi: 10.1097/MED.0b013e32834c800d. PMID: 21986512","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58005"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15892"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58005","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58005"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-21T22:51:43+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T15:44:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8583"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72535"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"3618","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/3618"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Placental function","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-09-23T09:31:53+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-09-23T09:31:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","